# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Maraimalai Murasu — Production Environment Variables
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy this file to `.env.production` (drop the .example) and fill in the
# real values BEFORE running `npm run build`. Vite bakes these values into
# the final JS bundle, so they need to be set at build time, not runtime.

# The URL of your backend Ads/Content API on Hostinger.
# Use HTTPS (not HTTP) to avoid mixed-content warnings on a secure site.
# Examples:
#   Same domain, subpath: https://maraimalaimurasu.com/api
#   Subdomain:            https://api.maraimalaimurasu.com
VITE_ADS_API=https://maraimalaimurasu.com/api

# The admin token. MUST match the ADMIN_TOKEN env var on the server.
# Generate something strong — at least 24 random characters.
# Anyone who reads this token from the JS bundle can write to your API,
# so treat it like a low-sensitivity password. For higher security, build
# a real login system.
VITE_ADS_API_TOKEN=CHANGE_ME_TO_SOMETHING_STRONG_LIKE_mm2026XyZ7qPq8tRkL3vN
